<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-12-28T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-12-28T20:00:00-05:00" n="807" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/83: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-12-29T09:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">December 29,
                                        1926—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 29—6:03
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>645. My telegram number 641, December 27, 4 p.m. At a meeting of
                            interested Ministers yesterday afternoon Italian Minister was persuaded
                            to make possible the necessary unanimity with regard to rendition of the
                            Mixed Court by acceding to compromise proposal suggested by the consular
                            body at Shanghai with respect to the selection of senior consul’s
                            deputies. It is therefore expected rendition can be effected January
                            1st.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>